A pair of gutsy acrobats have crossed Zimbabwe's awe-inspiring Victoria Falls on a tightrope.

Lukas Irmler from Germany and Reinhard Kleindl from Austria completed the 328ft crossing on a slack line, after negotiating with officials for several months to get permission.

They both made the crossing without falling off, ultimately not using the safety cords attached to the line.

Mr Irmler told Sky News: 'Here you have a lot of spray, a lot of water in the air, floating beside you, splashing your face and it's intimidating on the one side but also distracting.

