'You need to have a clear visual view of the environment, you need to be focused on the anchor point to the very end you want to walk to and not get distracted by a lot of water crashing by the side, which is very hard mentally.'

Mr Kleindl added: 'Optically it's very difficult because the spray comes from the sides and it's like waves, they try to drag you, so it's really difficult for the optics and obviously everything is very heavy because it's soaked with water.'

While it is neither the highest nor the widest waterfall in the world, it is classified as the largest, based on its width of 5,604ft and height of 354ft.

